        "content": "<p>darinmorrison <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317#issuecomment-598914179\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317#issuecomment-598914179\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317\">Issue #1317</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It might be a good idea to add a separate section for <code>[*.c]</code> files and perhaps others if necessary.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 190555581,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1584134063
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>sunfishcode <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317#issuecomment-598927510\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317#issuecomment-598927510\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317\">Issue #1317</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>One thing I'm unclear on about editorconfig files; we already have a .rustfmt file, and we use all default settings; shouldn't we expect editors to either read the .rustfmt file, or at least default to rustfmt's defaults?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 190558984,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1584136300
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>bjorn3 <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317#issuecomment-599122572\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317#issuecomment-599122572\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317\">Issue #1317</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>.editorconfig</code> is meant to be supported by all editors, not just those that support rust. It also applies to all text files, not only rust files.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 190609322,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1584212897
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>darinmorrison <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317#issuecomment-599123073\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317#issuecomment-599123073\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317\">Issue #1317</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>@sunfishcode the <code>.rustfmt</code> is good but only applies to Rust files. Other things like <code>.c</code> or <code>.wat</code> or random text files won't get the benefit from that configuration.</p>\n<p>The main thing I find useful about having the <code>.editorconfig</code> is that line endings are configured project-wide. I often use windows for development and prefer not to force the editor to <code>LF</code> globally since I sometimes edit system files as well. It's not critical or anything, just nice to have.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 190609482,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1584213123
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>abrown <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317#issuecomment-599309244\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317#issuecomment-599309244\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317\">Issue #1317</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I think this might be extra-helpful if it told IDEs to wrap lines to a certain length; I tend to forget to do that for non-Rust files.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 190678718,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1584325604
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>sunfishcode <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317#issuecomment-600902453\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317#issuecomment-600902453\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317\">Issue #1317</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>For LF line endings, should we add a .gitattributes file containing <code>* text=auto eol=lf</code>? That way git would handle it automatically for all text files, not just files created by editorconfig-aware editors.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 191054293,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1584572852
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>darinmorrison <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317#issuecomment-600909952\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317#issuecomment-600909952\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317\">Issue #1317</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Yeah the <code>.gitattributes</code> approach would also work for that. For reference, here is the <a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/master/.gitattributes\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/master/.gitattributes\">rust-lang/rust/.gitattributes</a> which does that.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 191056667,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1584574567
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>darinmorrison edited a <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317#issuecomment-600909952\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317#issuecomment-600909952\">comment</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317\">Issue #1317</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Yeah the <code>.gitattributes</code> approach would also work for that. For reference, here is the <a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/master/.gitattributes\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/master/.gitattributes\"><code>rust-lang/rust/.gitattributes</code></a> which does that.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 191056684,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1584574596
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>sunfishcode <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317#issuecomment-601897916\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317#issuecomment-601897916\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1317\">Issue #1317</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I submitted #1370 to add a .gitattributes file, following your suggestion.</p>\n<p>If anyone has a clear need for a .editorconfig file beyond that, we can add it, but otherwise my sense is to wait until we have one. <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1365\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1365\">https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/1365</a> has now removed most of the remaining C++ code from the repo, which further simplifies things.</p>\n</blockquote>",
